        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Vana est sine viribus ira. Nihil firmum sine certis vinculis: nihil potens sine armato exercitu. Si cogere potuisset senatores, 
                        simplicis erat rogare: et fiduciam ponere in populo inermi, spes desperata. In extremis, nihil fidendum, non aliqua obstrictum 
                        necessitate.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Anger without force is futile. Nothing is solid without sure bonds, nothing [is] powerful without a well-equipped army. 
                If one could force the senators, asking it would be na√Øve, and it is hopeless to place trust in an unarmed people. 
                In the most dangerous circumstances one should rely on anything that is not secured by some sort of necessity.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
